explanation: Classic dynamic programming on two strings. dp[i][j] stores the minimal deletion cost for prefixes s1[0..i-1] and s2[0..j-1]. When characters match, no cost is added; otherwise choose the cheaper of deleting from s1 or s2. Uses O(m*n) memory but can be reduced to O(min(m,n)) with rolling arrays.

